{
  "texts": [
    "To facilitate the determination of DH parameters, a coordinate frame is assigned to each joint, with the z i axis of the frame aligned with the direction of the joint's rotation or sliding motion [37].",
    "This alignment simplifies the computation of the transformation matrices by reducing the number of non-zero elements, thereby making the kinematic equations more tractable.The application of the DH parameters involves a series of homogeneous transformation matrices, each representing the relative position and orientation between consecutive links.",
    "These matrices are then multiplied together to obtain the final transformation matrix, which describes the pose of the end-effector in the base frame.",
    "This systematic approach not only streamlines the computation but also ensures consistency and accuracy in the kinematic analysis of complex robotic systems.In summary, the forward kinematics algorithm accepts the joint degrees of freedom as inputs and computes the homogeneous transformation matrix, which represents the position and orientation of the robotic arm's end-effector, as the output.",
    "This process is fundamental for determining the spatial configuration of robotic manipulators based on their joint parameters."
  ]
}